result.execSummary:
The defendant Antoine Dechester Gail was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Antoine Dechester Gail is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Antoine Dechester Gail was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: ADMINISTRATIVE STAY ALLOWING DEFENDANT UNTIL     01-14-2016     TO PAY FINE AND COSTS, GRANTED.

Defendant Antoine Dechester Gail in court with attorney Joel Alan Mogren.  Sarra Mae Kiaie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
CASE HEARD FOR BRANCH 40.
State is unable to proceed as to count 1, Battery.  Case set for jury trial.  State's essential witness failed to appear.  State has no alternative theory of prosecution.  Defense motion to dismiss is granted by the Court without prejudice.
AS to count 2:  On state's motion, Court ordered charge AMENDED to Disorderly Conduct, Co. Ord. 63.01 to which defendant pled no contest.
Court found defendant guilty and ordered defendant to pay a forfeiture of $100.00 including all costs and surcharges by 12-14-2015 or a civil judgment shall be entered.
